article.headline: Jacksonville 70, Stetson 58
article.story: DELAND, Fla. (AP) -- Antonio Cool scored 16 points and Haminn Quaintance grabbed 13 rebounds to lead Jacksonville to a 70-58 victory over Stetson on Wednesday night. Jesse Kimbrough and B.J. Surry each contributed 15 points for the Dolphins (10-8, 6-5 Atlantic Sun), who won for the fifth time in their last six games. Ljubisa Vrcelj added nine points and 10 rebounds for Jacksonville. E.J. Gordon led Stetson (7-11, 5-6) with 15 points but made just 4-of-16 shots from the floor. The Hatters also got 14 points from Borislav Djordjic and 13 from Anthony Register as Stetson shot just 33.9 percent on the night. Kimbrough hit 9-of-11 free throws in the second half as Jacksonville held Stetson to no field goals for nearly nine minutes down the stretch. The win was coach Hugh Durham's 100th at Jacksonville and puts him eight victories shy of breaking Rollie Rourke's school-record of 107 victories. Durham has 627 wins overall. Jacksonville played without David Lee, who averages 11.8 points. He was out with a lower stomach injury, snapping a streak of 45 starts.
